# 🤖 Multi-Agent Code Review System

A powerful AI-powered code review system built with **LangGraph** and **Google Gemini** that uses multiple specialized agents to analyze your codebase for security vulnerabilities, architecture issues, and code quality problems.

---

## 🧠 How It Works

The system uses a **multi-agent graph** powered by [LangGraph](https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph) where three specialized AI agents run in parallel to review your code:

```
Your Codebase
      │
      ▼
 File Scanner
      │
      ▼
┌─────┴──────┐
│            │
▼            ▼            ▼
Security   Architecture  Code Quality
 Agent       Agent         Agent
│            │              │
└─────┬──────┘──────────────┘
      │
      ▼
  Reporter
      │
      ▼
 JSON + Markdown Reports
```

### 🕵️ Agents

| Agent | Responsibilities |
|-------|-----------------|
| 🔐 **Security Agent** | Detects hardcoded credentials, SQL injection, shell injection, `eval()` usage, insecure deserialization, and more |
| 🏛️ **Architecture Agent** | Identifies God classes, tight coupling, missing abstractions, circular dependencies, and design pattern violations |
| ✨ **Code Quality Agent** | Finds unused variables, deeply nested code, long functions, missing docstrings, and style issues |

